A minimalistic scene of a single empty leather executive chair at the head of a long polished mahogany boardroom table, viewed from the far end of the table. On the table, a single elegant analog clock lies flat, its hands frozen at a sharp angle. The room is bathed in soft, warm natural light streaming through floor-to-ceiling windows showing an abstract cityscape. The composition emphasizes the vast negative space of the empty table surface, creating tension and anticipation. Muted color palette of deep browns, cream, and subtle gold accents.
